The paper discusses the multiprocessor effect and scaling models used in industry and academia for estimating multiprocessor capacity. This topic falls under the area of performance evaluation and analysis, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.PF (Performance), followed by cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper's focus on queueing theory and multiprocessor performance evaluation suggests that it is more likely to be classified under cs.PF, but it also touches on hardware architecture and distributed computing, which are covered by the other sub-categories listed.
